HEADWORD: Soporate
<hw>Sop"o*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>soporatus</ets>, p. p. or <ets>soporare</ets> to put to sleep, fr.
<ets>sopor</ets> a heavy sleep.]</ety> <def>To lay or put to sleep; to
stupefy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soporiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
